Peru Stocks: Candente, La Cima, Cementos Lima, IRL, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-22T21:26:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/peru-stocks-candente-la-cima-cementos-lima-irl-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a third session, dropping
0.4 percent to 19,149.90. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose
0.2 percent to 2,473.95.  Industrial and mining stocks declined on investor concern
over the policies of President-elect Ollanta Humala, said Banco
de Credito analyst Daniela Door. Humala is scheduled to take
office July 28.  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAI1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields
Ltd., plunged 17 percent to 4.15 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, fell 2.7
percent to $1.07.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian
exploration company, dropped 2.3 percent to $1.30 after copper
declined in  London .  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the
country’s biggest cement maker, slid 2 percent to 2.45 soles.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 1.8 percent to 1.66 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
